@page
@model FAQModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "FAQ";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Welcome to our Music Library FAQ page! Here you'll find answers to some common questions. If you don't see your question here, feel free to contact us.</p>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>1. What is this Music Library?</h2>
    <p>Our Music Library is a platform designed for music enthusiasts to discover, organize, and listen to a vast range of music. It offers user-friendly tools for cataloging and managing personal music collections online.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>2. How do I search for music in the library?</h2>
    <p>You can search for music by typing the album name into the search bar at the top of the page. Use filters to narrow down your results even further.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>3. Can I upload my own music?</h2>
    <p>Currently, our platform does not support user uploads. However, you can add music from our existing catalog to your personal playlists or favorites list.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>4. Is there a dark mode?</h2>
    <p>No, our Music Library does not support dark mode. We've focused on a bright, clear design to enhance readability and user experience.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>5. How do I add music to my favorites?</h2>
    <p>Simply click the heart icon next to any song, album, or artist to add them to your “Favorites” list for quick access.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>6. Can I download songs from the library?</h2>
    <p>You can't download audio files directly, but you can export song information as a CSV file. This CSV file includes details such as song title, artist, album, and genre, which you can use for cataloging or importing into other tools. Just look for the “Export to CSV” option in your library or playlist section.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>7. How does the "Order By" filter work?</h2>
    <p>The "Order By" filter helps you sort your search results based on different criteria. You can choose to organize music by:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Title</strong> - Alphabetically sorts by the song, album, or artist title.</li>
        <li><strong>Artist</strong> - Groups and orders songs by artist name.</li>
        <li><strong>Release Date</strong> - Shows the newest or oldest music first.</li>
        <li><strong>Genre</strong> - Organizes music based on genre categories.</li>
        <li><strong>Popularity</strong> - Lists songs based on their popularity or top listens.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Simply select your preferred "Order By" option in the filter menu to view your music in the order that suits you best!</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>8. Does the Music Library provide statistics?</h2>
    <p>Yes! Our Music Library offers detailed statistics to help you explore your listening habits. You can view stats like:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Most Played Songs</strong> -See your top tracks based on play count.</li>
        <li><strong>Top Artists</strong>- Discover which artists you listen to most frequently.</li>
        <li><strong>Genre Breakdown</strong> - Get an overview of the genres you listen to the most.</li>
        <li><strong>Listening History</strong> - Track your listening activity over time.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Access these stats in the “My Stats” section to gain insights into your music preferences!</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>9. Is there a mobile app available?</h2>
    <p>Currently, we're focused on optimizing the website experience, but a mobile app is in development. Stay tuned for announcements!</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <h2>10. How do I report a technical issue?</h2>
    <p>If you encounter any technical issues, please contact our customer support team directly at <a href="mailto:support@musiclibrary.com">support@musiclibrary.com</a>. We're here to help!</p>
</div>

<p>If you have any other questions, please reach out through our <a href="contact.html">Contact Page</a>.</p>

